The software deficiencies were particularly important, as the class Baden-Wuerttemberg ships will be operated by a crew of about 120 sailors: half the crew of the old class Bremen ships.
It was also found that the ship has an excessive weight, which reduces its performance and limits the Navy &apos; s ability to add future upgrades.
